<i>Hi, Paul.</i>

40:39.290 --> 40:42.750
Listen, I'm calling you because,
you know, the Berg painting,

40:42.950 --> 40:44.710
the one that Rita loves?

40:44.910 --> 40:47.320
<i>I'll be willing to give you</i>
<i>a pandemic discount.</i>

40:47.520 --> 40:50.060
- Well, I think we should hang on
to the cash

40:50.260 --> 40:52.720
<i>that we have right now.</i>

40:52.910 --> 40:53.720
<i>So should you, my friend.</i>

40:53.920 --> 40:55.940
You're a smart man.

40:56.140 --> 40:58.850
You're wonderful friend Paul is
not coming through on anything.

40:59.050 --> 41:01.590
He's totally out.

41:01.790 --> 41:04.290
<i>- Oh, well, he is wonderful</i>
<i>because he introduced us.</i>

41:04.490 --> 41:06.210
You know what's coming up,
cupcake?

41:06.410 --> 41:09.340
<i>Bankruptcy. Homelessness.</i>

41:09.540 --> 41:10.950
<i>I wish I had a bigger car</i>
<i>to live in.</i>

41:11.150 --> 41:13.690
No, it's my birthday.

41:13.890 --> 41:16.350
- Parts.
- Fridge parts. Oh, finally.

41:16.550 --> 41:18.180
<i>I know. Yeah.</i>

41:18.370 --> 41:20.570
Next week, right?

41:20.770 --> 41:22.530
You're 45.

41:22.730 --> 41:24.440
<i>- No, it's my 40th,</i>
<i>and it's tomorrow.</i>

41:24.640 --> 41:27.400
You don't have to add
five years.

41:27.600 --> 41:28.620
<i>I was just teasing you.</i>

41:28.820 --> 41:29.840
I remember.

41:30.040 --> 41:32.350
And I got you something.

41:35.310 --> 41:38.460
Yep, you're going to love it.

41:38.660 --> 41:40.280
<i>What am I going to love?</i>

41:41.450 --> 41:43.160
- You'll see.
It's a surprise.

41:43.360 --> 41:45.990
<i>- You know what would be</i>
<i>a really nice surprise</i>

41:46.190 --> 41:49.640
<i>is if you can show up for my</i>
<i>Zoom birthday party tomorrow.</i>

41:49.840 --> 41:52.990
<i>Paul's going to be there.</i>
<i>Tony's going to be there.</i>

41:53.190 --> 41:54.780
<i>I understand you're probably</i>
<i>having dinner with the family,</i>

41:54.980 --> 41:59.040
<i>but if you could just</i>
<i>slip out for five minutes...</i>

41:59.240 --> 42:03.570
- That would be dangerous
and exciting.

42:03.770 --> 42:05.700
<i>I would love it.</i>

42:05.900 --> 42:07.520
Hello?

42:09.040 --> 42:10.360
- Hello?
- Hello?

42:10.560 --> 42:12.710
<i>Hello?</i>

42:12.910 --> 42:15.230
Hello?

42:15.430 --> 42:16.800
What's up?

42:17.000 --> 42:19.190
- So, I heard
it's your "B" day tomorrow.

42:19.390 --> 42:22.190
Well, I think
we should celebrate.

42:23.930 --> 42:26.680
- You know, I was just
going to lay low.

42:26.880 --> 42:27.940
Well, think about it.

42:28.140 --> 42:29.460
- Okay.
- Okay.

42:29.660 --> 42:31.030
- Alright, thanks.
- Bye.

42:31.230 --> 42:32.900
- Okay, let me know
about the fridge.

42:33.100 --> 42:35.420
- Sure. Thank you.
- Okay. Bye.

42:36.510 --> 42:42.650
[ Cheers and applause ]

42:42.850 --> 42:47.180
Listen to them clap, Rita.

42:47.380 --> 42:51.740
Clapping for the nurses
and the first responders.

42:53.870 --> 42:55.920
[ Speaks indistinctly ]

43:04.490 --> 43:07.670
♪

43:30.040 --> 43:33.790
- Hey, listen, I was thinking
we may be able to sell

43:33.990 --> 43:35.830
that Berg painting to Waterman.

43:36.030 --> 43:38.660
You know, that rich friend
of my dad's?

43:38.860 --> 43:41.410
I don't mind.
I can call him.

43:41.600 --> 43:43.100
You'd do that for me?

43:43.300 --> 43:45.100
Of course I would.

43:51.580 --> 43:54.200
Who's texting you at this hour?

43:54.400 --> 43:58.640
- It's an artist,
Barry Marlowe.

43:58.840 --> 44:02.120
He's kind of a pain in the ass.

44:02.320 --> 44:04.470
He says he loves me, but

44:04.670 --> 44:06.810
I think he wants
something from me.

44:15.560 --> 44:18.750
You never asked me for anything,
have you?

44:18.950 --> 44:20.520
That you stay healthy.

44:33.060 --> 44:35.850
- I'm sorry, babe.
I'm so tired tonight.

44:36.050 --> 44:37.940
I can't.

44:38.140 --> 44:41.640
- Oh, it's -- it's fine.

44:41.840 --> 44:45.730
We have tomorrow,
tomorrow, and tomorrow.

44:45.930 --> 44:47.510
And the next day.

45:04.170 --> 45:06.580
<i>- The number of confirmed cases</i>
<i>of COVID-19 in the U.S.</i>

45:06.780 --> 45:09.010
<i>now tops 83,000,</i>

45:09.210 --> 45:10.970
<i>more than have been recorded</i>
<i>in China or Italy</i>

45:11.170 --> 45:12.580
<i>and continue to grow.</i>

45:12.780 --> 45:14.760
<i>Over 1,100 people here</i>
<i>have died</i>

45:14.960 --> 45:16.670
<i>from the coronavirus</i>
<i>so far.</i>

45:16.870 --> 45:20.110
<i>With vaccines still in</i>
<i>development, and no...ready,</i>

45:20.310 --> 45:21.720
<i>the CDC and</i>
<i>top medical experts say</i>

45:21.920 --> 45:23.860
<i>that masks</i>
<i>and social distancing</i>

45:24.060 --> 45:26.860
<i>are the only way to curb</i>
<i>the wave of infections.</i>

45:27.060 --> 45:30.820
<i>- Whenever we put the clamps</i>
<i>down and shut everything down,</i>

45:31.020 --> 45:32.430
<i>we do it for two reasons.</i>

45:32.630 --> 45:35.520
You're up early.

45:35.720 --> 45:37.000
Yeah, I got up at 4:00.

45:37.200 --> 45:39.260
- I couldn't sleep.
- I know.

45:39.460 --> 45:43.660
- I can't tell what's paid
and what's not paid.

45:43.860 --> 45:46.000
- See, there's a little "P"
on the back.

46:04.890 --> 46:07.730
♪ Happy Birthday to you

46:07.930 --> 46:11.950
♪ Happy Birthday,
dear Clarissa ♪

46:12.150 --> 46:13.990
♪ Happy Birthday to you
[ Doorbell rings ]

46:14.190 --> 46:16.520
- Oh, hang on, hang on.
Doorbell.

46:16.720 --> 46:19.640
Oh, hang on. Gloves.

46:20.860 --> 46:22.640
One sec. Coming.

46:28.690 --> 46:31.660
- Happy birthday to the most
vibrant woman that I know.

46:31.860 --> 46:33.230
Thank you, Paul.

46:33.430 --> 46:36.220
So what's your plan today?

46:38.270 --> 46:40.060
I don't know.

46:40.260 --> 46:43.540
Jonathan is supposed to be
showing some sign of life,

46:43.740 --> 46:46.550
<i>but he's not here.</i>

46:46.750 --> 46:47.720
Oh.

46:47.920 --> 46:49.850
So, you know when you have

46:50.050 --> 46:52.470
one of those real assholes
for a student?

46:52.670 --> 46:56.730
This time he's saying that
the U.N. is completely defunct

46:56.930 --> 46:59.730
because it doesn't do anything
to support its mandate.

46:59.930 --> 47:02.910
- He's right. He's right.
He's absolutely right.

47:03.110 --> 47:05.480
<i>International organizations</i>
<i>are obsolete</i>

47:05.680 --> 47:07.350
<i>in concept and in function.</i>

47:07.550 --> 47:09.050
<i>- Okay.</i>
- Yeah.

47:09.250 --> 47:10.350
<i>So this is your new opinion?</i>

47:10.550 --> 47:11.530
- Oh, come on.
Everything goes back

47:11.730 --> 47:13.360
to the very root
of all problems,

47:13.560 --> 47:15.310
and that is that
the majority of the people

47:15.510 --> 47:17.970
are just plain stupid.

47:18.170 --> 47:21.020
<i>Oh, and, by the way,</i>
<i>Rita says, "Happy 40th."</i>

47:21.220 --> 47:24.370
- Oh, good. So she can count.
That's great.

47:24.570 --> 47:26.590
<i>Listen to me, please.</i>

47:26.790 --> 47:28.810
<i>You hired me to help</i>
<i>take care of your money.</i>

47:29.010 --> 47:30.460
<i>I'm your accountant.</i>

47:30.660 --> 47:32.240
<i>The overall picture's</i>
<i>not bright.</i>

47:32.440 --> 47:34.290
<i>Money's not coming in.</i>
<i>You're two months overdue,</i>

47:34.490 --> 47:38.160
<i>as you know, on your rent,</i>
<i>and nothing is being sold.</i>

47:38.360 --> 47:41.210
- So what do are saying?
I just have to close down?

47:41.410 --> 47:43.690
<i>- Exactly.</i>
<i>Take advantage of this moment</i>

47:43.890 --> 47:46.740
<i>to close everything</i>
<i>down permanently.</i>

47:46.940 --> 47:48.220
<i>You know, you're lucky.</i>
<i>Everybody else --</i>

47:48.420 --> 47:51.260
- I'm lucky? I should
consider myself lucky?

47:51.460 --> 47:53.700
- James, how about being
a little more tactful?

47:53.900 --> 47:55.830
We're talking
about his life here.

47:56.030 --> 47:58.740
- Thank you, Sue.
- That's okay, honey.

48:02.310 --> 48:03.880
- [ Doorbell rings ]
- Hello?!

49:05.630 --> 49:10.910
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

49:11.110 --> 49:13.390
What? Sorry.

49:13.590 --> 49:18.570
♪ Happy Birthday to me

49:18.770 --> 49:23.650
♪ Happy Birthday to me

49:27.000 --> 49:29.750
I'm just calling to thank you
for this

49:29.950 --> 49:32.930
amazing birthday gift.

49:33.130 --> 49:36.500
Happy Birthday, Cherry Slush.

49:36.700 --> 49:39.680
Yeah, you know,
people are taking up hobbies

49:39.880 --> 49:43.810
and trying to cook,
so I figured you might...

49:44.010 --> 49:44.990
Can I just tell you
what happened,

49:45.190 --> 49:46.990
just spread the pain
around a bit?

49:47.190 --> 49:50.420
<i>- Sure, but when</i>
<i>are you coming by?</i>

49:52.290 --> 49:54.520
<i>- I think</i>
<i>that would be torture.</i>

49:54.720 --> 49:56.210
<i>I mean, we can't hug,</i>

49:56.410 --> 49:58.770
<i>we can't kiss,</i>
<i>we can't make love.</i>

50:02.430 --> 50:05.090
I can't do that to my wife.

50:05.290 --> 50:08.440
She's had asthma her whole life.
Blah, blah, blah.

50:08.640 --> 50:10.880
<i>But, you know,</i>
<i>sometimes I feel sorry for her.</i>

50:11.080 --> 50:14.540
<i>I mean, sometimes</i>
<i>really sorry for her.</i>

50:14.740 --> 50:17.500
Jonathan, every time we speak,

50:17.700 --> 50:21.500
it feels like we're just going
around and around and around.

50:21.700 --> 50:25.240
- Yeah, I thought you liked
going around with me.

50:25.440 --> 50:28.720
Around and around
and around and around.

50:35.980 --> 50:37.900
Hello.

50:45.820 --> 50:49.090
Honey! Listen to this!

50:49.290 --> 50:51.180
"Peace cannot be kept by force.

50:51.380 --> 50:55.230
It can only be achieved
by understanding."

50:55.430 --> 50:56.360
Einstein.

50:56.560 --> 50:59.970
Or Frankenstein.

51:00.170 --> 51:03.540
"True peace is not just
the absence of conflict,

51:03.740 --> 51:06.370
but the presence of justice."

51:06.570 --> 51:08.330
Honey!

51:08.530 --> 51:12.930
"Therefore, wherever you
find peace, you find harmony."

51:16.200 --> 51:17.770
Honey!
[ Ringtone playing ]

51:23.860 --> 51:27.220
Yes. Hello? Speaking.

51:27.420 --> 51:29.220
What do you mean
she's worse?

51:29.420 --> 51:32.090
Well, how much worse?

51:32.290 --> 51:34.180
Yes, I know that
you do not allow guests.

51:34.380 --> 51:36.090
I've been informed of that.

51:38.440 --> 51:39.740
Okay.

51:49.580 --> 51:50.980
That would be amazing.

51:51.180 --> 51:53.280
- That's another thing
that could be done.

51:56.760 --> 51:58.630
Rita?

52:02.680 --> 52:03.990
- Hey.
- Hey.

52:04.190 --> 52:07.130
Hi, hon, I was just
asking Harry...

52:07.330 --> 52:08.650
- Harry?
- ...if we could use

52:08.850 --> 52:10.170
his dumpster tomorrow
when the gardener comes.

52:10.370 --> 52:13.350
- Honey, I just spoke
to Heaven Meadows,

52:13.550 --> 52:17.180
and they said that

52:17.380 --> 52:20.320
they don't think
Mom will survive.

52:20.510 --> 52:23.140
- Anyway, thank you for the
birthday flowers, by the way.

52:23.340 --> 52:24.580
They're lovely.

52:24.780 --> 52:26.760
<i>Right. You're welcome.</i>

52:26.960 --> 52:31.110
<i>My friends just told me</i>
<i>that his wife had died,</i>

52:31.310 --> 52:33.630
<i>and it was a relief.</i>

52:33.830 --> 52:34.890
Dad.

52:35.090 --> 52:37.030
<i>When you're younger...</i>

52:37.230 --> 52:39.850
- Yeah?
<i>- ...yum, yum, yum. But...</i>

52:42.070 --> 52:43.900
Hang on. There's...

52:44.100 --> 52:47.470
There's something...

52:47.670 --> 52:50.350
<i>- What's going on?</i>
- Oh, nothing.

52:50.540 --> 52:53.170
<i>- Oh, yes, there is.</i>
- No.

53:17.670 --> 53:26.720
[ Playing piano ]

53:44.870 --> 53:48.090
Hey. Made you some tea.

53:51.180 --> 53:52.710
Why don't you try again?

53:52.910 --> 53:55.540
Playing always cheers you up.

53:55.740 --> 53:57.280
I can't.

53:57.480 --> 53:59.760
Tell me something.

53:59.960 --> 54:02.330
Is Harry a little lonely
after his wife left?

54:02.530 --> 54:03.640
Why are you asking me?

54:03.840 --> 54:06.380
I have no idea.

54:06.580 --> 54:09.720
- Well, I think I'm going
a little insane, you know?

54:11.900 --> 54:13.860
I'm worried about Mom.

54:14.060 --> 54:16.250
It's okay. Don't worry.

54:20.030 --> 54:22.220
Cheers. Cheers.

54:22.420 --> 54:23.960
<i>Hey, Happy Birthday, love.</i>

54:24.160 --> 54:25.740
<i>Happy Birthday.</i>

54:25.940 --> 54:28.570
- So, hey guys, looks like
we've got a special guest.

54:28.770 --> 54:30.660
Say hi to everyone, Mom.

54:30.860 --> 54:32.800
<i>How nice.</i>

54:32.990 --> 54:34.100
Thank you.

54:34.300 --> 54:36.580
- Cheers.
<i>- Thank you.</i>

54:36.780 --> 54:37.760
- Alright, we're wrapping it up,
but I'll give you a call later.

54:37.960 --> 54:39.800
<i>Good to see you.</i>

54:40.000 --> 54:41.760
<i>- Okay.</i>
- Okay.

54:41.960 --> 54:43.330
<i>Where is Jonathan?</i>

54:43.530 --> 54:45.720
<i>- Hey, where is Jonathan?</i>
<i>- Where's Jon?</i>

54:45.920 --> 54:48.890
<i>- Sometimes nothing</i>
<i>is better than something.</i>

54:50.500 --> 54:53.820
- Be that as it may,
it's getting very late,

54:54.020 --> 54:57.040
and we should probably
wrap it up.

54:57.240 --> 54:59.950
But thank you all so much
for coming.

55:00.150 --> 55:02.260
You really made my day.
Night.

55:02.460 --> 55:04.390
Wherever you are in the world.

55:04.590 --> 55:07.050
- Thank you. Thank you.
<i>- Alright, bye, everyone.</i>

55:07.250 --> 55:09.920
- Good night, good night.
<i>- Bye.</i>

55:10.120 --> 55:19.180
♪

55:38.810 --> 55:40.600
Oh, my gosh.

55:40.800 --> 55:41.950
- Hi.
- Hi.

55:42.150 --> 55:43.610
Brought you a cake.

55:43.800 --> 55:47.040
- Oh.
- I got you this

55:47.240 --> 55:51.180
- chocolate, black --
- No way. That's so sweet.

55:51.380 --> 55:52.830
- That's my favorite.
- Chocolate.

55:53.030 --> 55:54.310
Yum.

55:54.510 --> 55:56.270
Okay. Thank you.

55:56.470 --> 55:58.840
- You're welcome.
- Oh, yum.

55:59.040 --> 56:01.230
- 40, right?
- Yeah.

56:01.430 --> 56:04.060
- Do you want to come in?
- Yes, sure.

56:04.260 --> 56:05.630
- You haven't been anywhere,
have you?

56:05.830 --> 56:09.330
- No, no. I've been, like,
glued to your guesthouse.

56:09.530 --> 56:12.550
- Okay, so it's safe.
- Yeah.

56:12.750 --> 56:16.330
- Sure. Your dad's right here.
It's Ricky.

56:16.530 --> 56:19.510
- Hey, kid.
How's things in Chicago?

56:19.710 --> 56:21.460
Well, it's boring everywhere.

56:23.770 --> 56:26.560
Listen, just get yourself
a plane ticket

56:26.760 --> 56:29.780
and come home right now,
whatever it costs.

56:29.980 --> 56:32.130
- Oh, I just told Margo
the same thing.

56:32.330 --> 56:33.730
Yeah, I do.

56:35.520 --> 56:37.530
Take care, kid.

56:37.730 --> 56:39.010
- Hey, honey.
- Yes?

56:39.210 --> 56:41.970
- There's something
I want to run by you.

56:42.170 --> 56:43.800
You're a great mom.

56:44.000 --> 56:45.920
You're just noticing this now?

56:48.310 --> 56:50.370
You're funny, too.

56:50.570 --> 56:52.850
Are you okay?

56:53.050 --> 56:55.020
Do I not seem okay?

56:55.220 --> 56:59.330
- I've actually always been
fascinated by your culture.

56:59.530 --> 57:03.080
When I studied
the Greek-Persian Wars,

57:03.280 --> 57:05.640
I always rooted for you guys.

57:05.840 --> 57:09.520
- Well, the Persians,
they were great empire,

57:09.720 --> 57:11.000
one of the greatest.

57:11.200 --> 57:12.770
I really thank you.

57:14.340 --> 57:16.350
Let's make a toast.

57:16.550 --> 57:21.310
May life be safe, peaceful

57:21.510 --> 57:24.580
for the entire planet
and all its creatures.

57:24.780 --> 57:26.400
<i>Salamati.</i>

57:26.600 --> 57:28.490
- Oh, my God.
How did you know that?

57:28.690 --> 57:30.920
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

58:05.390 --> 58:07.840
<i>- The World Health Organization</i>
<i>remains concerned</i>

58:08.040 --> 58:09.710
<i>about the spreading</i>
<i>of COVID-19,</i>

58:09.910 --> 58:11.930
<i>particularly in</i>
<i>the developing countries.</i>

58:12.130 --> 58:13.800
<i>Call from Heaven Meadows.</i>

58:14.000 --> 58:16.020
Hello?

58:16.220 --> 58:17.540
<i>Professor Hasselberg?</i>

58:17.740 --> 58:19.200
Yes. Speaking.

58:19.390 --> 58:21.200
<i>- Dr. Camden</i>
<i>from Heaven Meadows.</i>

58:21.400 --> 58:25.940
<i>So pleased to let you know</i>
<i>that your mother has improved.</i>

58:26.140 --> 58:28.420
Oh, that's wonderful news.

58:28.620 --> 58:31.560
<i>- No more fever, and her</i>
<i>breathing is back to normal.</i>

58:31.760 --> 58:35.120
- Oh, that's just wonderful.
That's great.

58:35.320 --> 58:37.130
Please keep me in the loop.

58:37.330 --> 58:39.040
<i>Of course. Will do.</i>

58:39.240 --> 58:41.390
Thank you. Thank you.

58:41.590 --> 58:43.570
<i>- Bye-bye now.</i>

58:43.770 --> 58:45.870
<i>End of call.</i>

58:46.070 --> 58:47.620
<i>- The doctors don't have</i>
<i>enough equipment,</i>

58:47.810 --> 58:49.530
<i>- especially in the rural areas.</i>
- Honey,

58:49.730 --> 58:52.710
where are
those gluten-free muffins?

58:52.910 --> 58:55.930
The ones that you buy
all the time.

58:56.130 --> 58:58.450
- Honey!
- Yeah?

58:58.650 --> 59:01.280
- Honey, I have some great news
from Heavenly Meadows.

59:01.480 --> 59:02.530
Oh.

59:05.230 --> 59:13.550
[ Phone ringing ]

59:21.640 --> 59:23.780
What's up?

59:23.980 --> 59:26.610
- Hi. I've been looking for you.
- What?

59:26.810 --> 59:29.870
I can't hear you.

59:30.070 --> 59:32.790
It's a helicopter. I'm outside.

59:32.990 --> 59:37.010
I-I am sorry about yesterday,
okay?

59:37.210 --> 59:39.320
I-I really miss you.

59:39.520 --> 59:41.500
Maybe -- Maybe you could
make some pasta

59:41.690 --> 59:42.930
with that thing I got you.

59:43.130 --> 59:44.500
We could have dinner
in your garden,

59:44.700 --> 59:45.890
<i>you know, like,</i>
<i>at a safe distance.</i>

59:46.090 --> 59:48.760
- Is this your idea
of an apology?

59:48.960 --> 59:51.330
- No, it's not an apology.
It's just --

59:51.530 --> 59:54.120
It's just a suggestion.

59:54.320 --> 59:56.860
- I miss you.
- You do?

59:57.060 --> 59:59.210
